    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>129500</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#_ίππα"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">ίππα</seg></name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Να_" type="patronymic"><seg part="I">Να</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>  
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ippa fille de Na<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ippa daughter of Na<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>ippa figlia di Na<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Another possibility would be to read <foreign xml:lang="grc">-ίππαν Α-</foreign>, but the inscription was written on only one line and such an accusative 
               of the honoured person would normally be followed by the nominative of the dedicant (although there seems to exist one occurrence of an isolated accusative
               in <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.278.html">IRCyr2020 C.278</ref>). So we prefer the nominative as a caption for the associated image.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
